This paper focuses on the ranking of scholarly papers based on citation data, which is a common topic in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of metadata from the Microsoft Academic Graph, which could involve database systems (cs.DB) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) considerations.
